body:
Great work @guyuqi! Will try your PR.

My only concern is, this build probably fails on ppc64le due to the problem @evans-ye [mentioned before](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BIGTOP-3188?focusedCommentId=16793377&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-16793377). protoc binary was published on the maven central by your effort and grpc-java as well, but they may be reluctant to do the same thing for ppc64le, that is relatively minor platform.

@evans-ye @oflebbe @JunHe77 Is it possible for us to publish the next release without Zeppelin only on ppc64le? Should we vote on dev-ml?

@sekikn,  agree with you.
Google published protoc ppc64le binaries since [3.7.0](https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/google/protobuf/protoc/3.7.0/), 
but for protoc-gen-grpc-java, ppc64le binaries are still not available in the latest release [1.28.1](https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/grpc/protoc-gen-grpc-java/1.28.1/).
